FT  06 FEB 93 / US duties on British steel plate attacked
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IVOR OWEN, Parliamentary Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
US ACTION to impose heavy anti-dumping duties on British exports of steel
plate was 'unwarranted and wholly disproportionate,' Mr Richard Needham,
trade minister, said yesterday.
He said the provisional 109.22 per cent levy was in addition to the earlier
duties imposed on UK exports of plate and bar.
Mr Needham told the Commons: 'To penalise genuinely privatised companies
which have not received subsidies for over six years is unfair and
economically unsound.'
He said the action had been initiated by the 'highly protected US steel
industry' and would not help efforts to secure an international settlement
in the multi-lateral steel agreement negotiations.
