<HEADLINE>
FT  05 FEB 93 / UK Company News: Heavitree hit by bad debts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GRAHAM DELLER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
HEAVITREE Brewery, the USM-quoted pub operator, reported profits
substantially lower over the 12 months to October 31.
Although turnover improved 34 per cent to Pounds 8.38m (Pounds 6.28m), the
pre-tax line tumbled from Pounds 910,000 to Pounds 560,000.
Directors of the Devon-based group blamed the decline on 'settling down
costs' following the acquisition of its small managed estate and bad debts
which amounted to Pounds 344,000.
Interest charges on loans were 'exceptionally high', they added.
However, a recovery was under way and the recommended final dividend is held
at 2.45p for a maintained total of 3.05p, payable from earnings of 4.2p (8p)
per share.
