<HEADLINE>
FT  05 FEB 93 / UK Company News: Motor World valued at Pounds 27.7m in
launch
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER PEARSE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE 210p placing price of Motor World, announced yesterday, values the car
parts and accessories retailer at Pounds 27.7m.
Beeson Gregory is placing 5.97m ordinary shares of 20p, representing 45.3
per cent of the company's issued share capital.
Based on its pro forma earnings per share of 16p for the year to November 1,
the p/e multiple is 13.1 and the notional gross dividend yield 4 per cent.
Of the shares placed, 5.95m were new ordinaries and the balance were sold by
existing shareholders. Some Pounds 3.2m of the proceeds will go towards the
redemption of existing preference shares and about Pounds 9m to repay debt.
Dealings are expected to start on February 11.
Motor World grew from one motor accessories shop in Bradford in 1968. It now
has 180 outlets, mainly in the north of England, Wales and the Midlands, and
is planning to build a national network.
Mr Darrell Kershaw, managing director, has said that he believes the chain
could expand to 300 outlets within the next two years.
In the year to November 1 1992, pre-tax profits were Pounds 2.29m (Pounds
1.57m) on turnover of Pounds 34.2m (Pounds 28.7m).
</TEXT>
