FT  05 FEB 93 / Stockbroker barred
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE former head of a Manchester stockbroking firm has been barred by the
Securities and Futures Authority after he took Pounds 40,000 from an elderly
client's building society account to bolster his firm's capital.
